        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Roles_GetAllRoles",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve all role names associated with a specific application within a database that manages application roles. It takes an application name as input, identifies the corresponding application ID, and then fetches all roles linked to that application, ordering them by role name."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving basic SQL operations such as SELECT queries and conditional logic. It does not include complex joins, subqueries, or advanced SQL features, making it easy to understand and maintain."
        }
      ]
    },
